{
  "text": "A standard anterolateral viewing portal and anteromedial instrumentation portal are created at the joint line, lateral and medial to the patellar tendon, respectively. The knee joint is insufflated with normal saline, and a 4.0-mm, 30 arthroscope (Stryker Corporation) is used to visually inspect the intra-articular anatomy in a standard manner for diagnostic knee arthroscopy. [CITATION_1] Depending on the particular surgical indication, a variety of instrumentation may be used to address the respective pathology.",
